<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Billie Eilish has been lending her voice to the political causes closest to her heart, most recently backing Democratic presidential hopeful Joe Biden.</p>

<p>But the 18-year-old musician let her lust for fashion prevail on Thursday as she showcased her all Gucci outfit on Instagram.</p>

<p>'relax,' captioned Eilish, as she modeled the eclectic get-up for her 66.4millon followers.</p>

<p>Fashion first: Billie Eilish let her lust for fashion prevail on Thursday as she showcased her all Gucci outfit on Instagram</p>

<p>Billie showcased her iconic bright green roots, while rocking a pair of gold micro shades that featured a red tint.</p>

<p>She had the hood of her Gucci jacket over her head and she had a vibrant blue and red Gucci blanket wrapped around her body.</p>

<p>The Bad Guy songstress also wore a red turtle neck that had a crystal chain sewn into the collar. </p>

<p>Model behavior: 'relax,' captioned Eilish, as she modeled the eclectic get-up for her 66.4millon followers</p>

<p>As if her outfit were not gaudy enough, Eilish slipped her legs into a pair of bright red sweatpants that were obviously customized with various anime-inspired drawings.</p>

<p>The cartoon women on her pants were wearing brightly colored bikinis, which reflected the style of the streetwear brand Left Hand Los Angeles.</p>

<p>She slipped her feet into a pair of patent leather sneakers that featured chunky treads. </p>

<p>Only one of the shoes had a criss-cross strap with gold hardware.</p>

<p>Anime vibes: As if her outfit were not gaudy enough, Eilish slipped her legs into a pair of bright red sweatpants that were obviously customized with various anime-inspired drawings</p>

<p>Details: The cartoon women on her pants were wearing brightly colored bikinis, which reflected the style of the streetwear brand Left Hand Los Angeles</p>

<p>Just last month, Eilish spoke directly to voters before debuting her poignant single My Future at the 2020 Democratic National Convention.</p>

<p>She urged those tuning in to 'vote like our lives and the world depend on it,' while proudly endorsing Democratic presidential hopeful Joe Biden.</p>

<p> 'You don't need me to tell you things are a mess — Donald Trump is destroying our country and everything we care about,' began Eilish, who delivered her powerful speech against a purple backdrop.</p>

<p>Direct approach: Just last month, Eilish spoke directly to voters before debuting her poignant single My Future at the 2020 Democratic National Convention; Eilish pictured on August 19</p>

<p>For Biden: After listing the qualities she seeks in a leader, Billie voiced her support for Joe Biden and endorsed his capabilities as president; Biden pictured on September 9</p>

<p>The Bad Guy hitmaker directly called out President Donald Trump's ineffectiveness and stressed the importance of electing a leader that embodies true American values.</p>

<p>'We need leaders who will solve problems like climate change and covid — not deny them. Leaders who will fight against systemic racism and inequality.</p>

<p>'And that starts by voting for someone who understands how much is at stake; someone who is building a team that shares our values,' expressed Eilish passionately.</p>

<p>After listing the qualities she seeks in a leader, Billie voiced her support for Joe Biden and endorsed his capabilities as president. </p>

<p>Called out: The Bad Guy hitmaker directly called out President Donald Trump's ineffectiveness and stressed the importance of electing a leader that embodies true American values</p>

<p>Depend on it: 'We all have to vote like our lives and the world depend on it — because they do. The only way to be certain of our future is to make it ourselves. Please register; please vote,' concluded the Grammy winner</p>

<p>'It starts with voting against Donald Trump and for Joe Biden. Silence is not an option and we cannot sit this one out.'</p>

<p>Eilish closed out her powerful speech by encouraging citizens to vote with purpose and to ensure that they are registered to vote in their state.</p>

<p>'We all have to vote like our lives and the world depend on it — because they do. The only way to be certain of our future is to make it ourselves. Please register; please vote,' concluded the Grammy winner.</p>

<p>In her new track My Future, which she performed alongside brother and collaborator Finneas O'Connell, 23, Billie sang 'cause I'm in love with my future/Can't wait to meet her.' </p>

